---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path="/apps">
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path="/apps" />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="badge">Full rankings · 21 apps</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-4 text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl">Best Shopify SMS marketing apps ranked for 2026</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-orange-950/80">
        {site.heroPromise} This is the complete listicle: all 21 apps scored, compared in one table, with deep dives on the top ten.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-orange-950/75">
        Postscript is the SMS-native benchmark. {site.bestOverallReason} Klaviyo and Omnisend remain credible when SMS ships bundled with segmentation. The ranking below reflects consent discipline, cost-per-message economics, and Shopify event depth — not logo familiarity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      picks={[
        { label: 'Best SMS campaigns', tool: 'Postscript', reason: 'Drop access, VIP texts, restrained broadcasts for Shopify DTC' },
        { label: 'Best enterprise SMS', tool: 'Attentive', reason: 'High-volume promotional calendars with managed acquisition' },
        { label: 'Best lifecycle email', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Email strategy beside SMS — welcome, education, winback' },
        { label: 'Best data depth', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Segment-by-value and unified email-SMS when profiles justify cost' },
        { label: 'Best SMB bundled', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Email + SMS + push campaign calendar, fast install' },
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-14">
    <div class="card overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="badge">Comparison table</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-black text-slate-950">All 21 Shopify SMS marketing apps at a glance</h2>
      <table class="data-table mt-8">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>#</th>
            <th>App</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Pricing</th>
            <th>Shopify</th>
            <th>Automation</th>
            <th>Rating</th>
            <th>Review</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {rankedApps.map((app, i) => (
            <tr>
              <td class="font-black text-orange-700">{i + 1}</td>
              <td class="font-black text-slate-950">{app.name}</td>
              <td>{app.category}</td>
              <td>{app.pricing}</td>
              <td>{app.shopifyDepth}</td>
              <td>{app.automationDepth}</td>
              <td>★ {app.rating}</td>
              <td><a class="link" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>Review</a></td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-14">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="badge">Top 10 deep dives</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">Detailed reviews: ranks 1–10</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[17px] leading-8 text-orange-950/80">
        Each section below summarizes our independent workflow tests. Full 2,000+ word reviews with pricing breakdowns, migration notes, and eight FAQs live on individual app pages.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      {topTen.map((app, i) => (
        <ToolReview
          app={app}
          rank={i + 1}
          badge={i === 0 ? 'SMS campaign #1' : i === 1 ? 'Enterprise SMS #2' : i === 2 ? 'Lifecycle email #3' : undefined}
          paragraphs={listicleParagraphs[app.slug] || [app.shopifyFit, app.tagline, `Best for ${app.bestFor}.`]}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-14">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <p class="badge">Ranks 11–21</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">Specialists, suites, and stack pieces</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-[17px] leading-8 text-orange-950/80">
        The remaining apps are not "worse" — they solve narrower jobs. Mailchimp and Brevo for budget broadcasts. Postscript and Attentive for SMS. Justuno and Privy for capture. Rejoiner and Sendlane for guided migration. Click through for full reviews.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {rest.map((app, i) => (
        <a class="card" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>
          <span class="rank-pill">{i + 11}</span>
          <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-black text-slate-950">{app.name}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-orange-950/75">{app.category}</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-[16px] leading-7 text-orange-950/80">{app.tagline}</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-black text-slate-950">{app.pricing}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <article class="prose-shopify card">
      <h2>How to pick from this ranked list without analysis paralysis</h2>
      <p>Start with the bottleneck, not the brand name. If the list is too small, Privy or Justuno plus a lifecycle platform beats a premature Klaviyo migration. If cart recovery is the revenue leak, test Postscript or Recart alongside your email ESP before rip-and-replace. If reviews and loyalty drive repeat purchase, Yotpo or Marsello consolidation may beat best-in-class email alone.</p>
      <p>Run one workflow on paper before buying: trigger, audience, suppression, offer, product context, success metric, weekly owner. If the app cannot express that scenario cleanly, rank position does not matter. The homepage scoring rubric applies here — data depth, flow control, operating speed, measurement quality.</p>
      <p>Migration timing: never switch ESPs the week before Black Friday. Budget four weeks for mid-size stores, launch welcome first, validate cart second, add post-purchase third, winback last. Suppress recent purchasers across all flows during transition.</p>
      <h3>Stack patterns that work on Shopify</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Default SMS marketing stack:</strong> Postscript or Attentive SMS + Sequenzy lifecycle email</li>
        <li><strong>Data maximum:</strong> Klaviyo all-in with in-house retention lead</li>
        <li><strong>SMB speed:</strong> Omnisend + Justuno capture</li>
        <li><strong>Budget start:</strong> Shopify Email → Sequenzy + Postscript at 500+ orders/mo</li>
        <li><strong>Managed:</strong> Rejoiner or Sendlane when team bandwidth is the constraint</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  
    <div class="prose-shopify card mt-8">
      <h2>Campaign marketing depth: apps — index</h2>
      <p><strong>Scarcity Timing Discipline.</strong> Ember Ceramics (maker pottery drops, $38k/mo) plans 4,200 waitlist for 80 kiln pieces. Lesson: single VIP Postscript text sold out without code leaks. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Holdout Testing.</strong> Cipher Audio (high-AOV headphones, $320k/mo) plans launch sms to engaged browse-abandon only. Lesson: no launch discount — margin held at 58%. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Margin-After-Incentive Math.</strong> Patchwork Denim (upcycled fashion, $54k/mo) plans collection-specific drop sms by browse history. Lesson: tailored drops converted 4.1% vs 0.3% generic blasts. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Campaign Calendar Slots.</strong> Noir Collective (flash-sale streetwear, $240k/mo) plans thursday 6pm vip drop calendar. Lesson: revenue per send rose 31% after cutting broadcast frequency. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Offer Discipline Ladders.</strong> SoleDrop ATX (limited sneaker releases, $180k/mo) plans 11-minute size-run sell-through with waitlist priority. Lesson: VIP early link; general list email after 70% sell-through. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
      <p><strong>Segment-By-Value Quartiles.</strong> Festival Threads Co (tour merch, $95k/mo seasonal) plans geo-segmented tour sms by venue timezone. Lesson: 3 texts per city max during sale week. Postscript ranks #1 for SMS campaign execution; Attentive #2 enterprise; Sequenzy lifecycle email layer. Campaign marketers evaluating apps — index should map quarterly revenue moments before choosing software.</p>
